= 1.3
The temperature distribution in a thin isolated rod is $T_0 /(1+x^2)$ at a specific moment in time. Calculate the heat flux. In what way is it directed?
#solution[
The heat flux is 
$
  bold(j) = -lambda nabla T = (lambda 2x T_0)/(1+x^2)^2 bh(x)
$
The direction is $bh(x)$

]
